<definition>
  <statement>
      <term>Undercut</term> is a two player game between Rose and Colin. Each round, both players choose a number between <m>1</m> and <m>5</m> and simultaneously reveal their decisions. Let their decisions be <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> with <m>a \leq b</m>.
  </statement>
</definition>
<ul>
  <li> If <m>a+1 = b</m>, then the person who played <m>a</m> adds <m>a+b</m> to their score and the opponent gets nothing. </li>
  <li> Otherwise, each player adds their own number to their score. </li>
</ul>

<p>For example, if Rose plays <m>5</m> and Colin plays <m>3</m>, Rose gains <m>5</m> points and Colin gains <m>3</m> for a net difference of <m>+2</m> for Rose. But if Rose plays <m>5</m> and Colin plays <m>4</m>, Rose gets <m>0</m> points and Colin gets <m>9</m> for a net change of <m>-9</m> for Rose!
</p>

<question>
